{"id": "EUVD-2023-59831", "enisaUuid": "324bf80a-2a3d-3e1b-8a6a-8ce71a91cf4f", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: nvidia-shield: Reference hid_device devm allocation of input_dev name\n\nUse hid_device for devm allocation of the input_dev name to avoid a\nuse-after-free. input_unregister_device would trigger devres cleanup of all\nresources associated with the input_dev, free-ing the name. The name would\nsubsequently be used in a uevent fired at the end of unregistering the\ninput_dev.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:30", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-03T18:30:20", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b85d3807e5ec368bfd5b20245347d7c1434aff76", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/197d3143520fec9fde89aebabc9f0d7464f08e50", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53253"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53253"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "13bce637-bd02-3a6e-9322-fc5ff5817905", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.5.3"}, {"id": "3de992d4-cc65-3ca3-aff8-6ea3c2a41594", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6"}, {"id": "71e723ab-fba2-3b22-8e6d-689ce8f8300e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.5"}, {"id": "c391de77-5914-3079-a01a-53841f2a30dc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "e8a2926c-4fb8-3e41-af63-94ced5b582c4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "09308562d4afb1abc66366608fa1cb9de783272f <197d3143520fec9fde89aebabc9f0d7464f08e50"}, {"id": "fabda7a9-74ed-3be2-bbe1-99818274fd50", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "09308562d4afb1abc66366608fa1cb9de783272f <b85d3807e5ec368bfd5b20245347d7c1434aff76"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "2b48c6e3-a56c-3057-ab9c-29a6aae50b52", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}